e total pars of each round). E stands for even, which means the tournament was completed in the predetermined number of strokes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/golf/rules_and_equipment/4230206.stm |title=Scoring |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |accessdate=2008-09-20 | date=2005-09-13}}</ref>\n*{{note label|Note3|c|c}} The 1871 Open Championship was not held.<ref name=\"NotHeld\" />\n*{{note label|Note4|d|d}} Bob Martin won in a playoff against [[Davie Strath]] who refused to compete.\n*{{note label|Note5|e|e}} Willie Fernie won in a playoff against [[Bob Ferguson (golfer)|Bob Ferguson]].\n*{{note label|Note6|f|f}} Willie Park Jr. won in a playoff against [[Andrew Kirkaldy (golfer)|Andrew Kirkaldy]].\n*{{note label|Note7|g|g}} John Ball won The Open Championship as an amateur.\n*{{note label|Note8|h|h}} Harold Hilton won The Open Championship as an amateur.\n*{{note label|Note9|i|i}} Harry Vardon won in a playoff against [[John Henry Taylor]].\n*{{note label|Note10|j|j}} Harry Vardon won in a playoff against [[Arnaud Massy]].\n*{{note label|Note11|k|k}} The Open Championship was not held from 1915 to 1918 because of the [[World War I|First World War]].\n*{{note label|Note12|l|l}} Jock Hutchison won in a playoff against [[Roger Wethered]].\n*{{note label|Note13|m|m}} Bobby Jones won The Open Championship as an amateur.\n*{{note label|Note14|n|n}} Denny Shute won in a playoff against [[Craig Wood (golfer)|Craig Wood]].\n*{{note label|Note15|o|o}} The Open Championship was not held from 1940 to 1945 because of the [[World War II|Second World War]].\n*{{note label|Note16|p|p}} Bobby Locke won in a playoff against [[Harry Bradshaw (golfer)|Harry Bradshaw]].\n*{{note label|Note17|q|q}} Peter Thomson won in a playoff against [[Dave Thomas (golfer)|Dave Thomas]].\n*{{note label|Note18|r|r}} Bob Charles won in a playoff against [[Phil Rodgers]].\n*{{note label|Note19|s|s}} Jack Nicklaus won in a playoff against [[Doug Sanders]].\n*{{note label|Note20|t|t}} Tom Watson won in a playoff against [[Jack Newton]].\n*{{note label|Note21|u|u}} Mark Calcavecchia won in a playoff against [[Wayne Grady]] and [[Greg Norman]].\n*{{note label|Note22|v|v}} John Daly won in a playoff against [[Costantino Rocca]].\n*{{note label|Note23|w|w}} Mark O'Meara won in a playoff against [[Brian Watts]].\n*{{note label|Note24|x|x}} Paul Lawrie won in a playoff against [[Jean van de Velde (golfer)|Jean van de Velde]] and [[Justin Leonard]].\n*{{note label|Note25|y|y}} Ernie Els won in a playoff against [[Thomas Levet]], [[Steve Elkington]] and [[Stuart Appleby]].\n*{{note label|Note26|z|z}} Todd Hamilton won in a playoff against [[Ernie Els]].\n*{{note label|Note27|aa|aa}} P\u00e1draig Harrington won in a playoff against [[Sergio Garc\u00eda]].\n*{{note label|Note28|bb|bb}} Stewart Cink won in a playoff against [[Tom Watson (golfer)|Tom Watson]].\n*{{note label|Note29|cc|cc}} Zach Johnson won in a playoff against [[Marc Leishman]] and [[Louis Oosthuizen]].\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n'''General'''\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.opengolf.com/~/media/The%20Open/Information/Media_Guide.ashx |title=2011 Open Championship Media Guide |publisher=The Open Championship |accessdate=2011-08-20 |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806084256/http://www.opengolf.com/~/media/The%20Open/Information/Media_Guide.ashx |archivedate=2011-08-06 }}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.opengolf.com/en/History/OpenChampions.aspx |title=Open Champions |publisher=The Open Championship |accessdate=2011-08-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100302213551/http://www.opengolf.com/en/History/OpenChampions.aspx |archivedate=2010-03-02 }}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.opengolf.com/en/History/PreviousOpens.aspx |title=Previous Opens |publisher=The Open Championship |accessdate=2011-08-20 }}\n'''Specific'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.opengolf.com/ The Open Championship official site]\n*[http://www.randa.